# General rule of wildcards (globbing)
* any character
? any single character
[characters] any character that is a member of the character set
[!characters] any character that is NOT a member of the character set
[[:class:]] any character that is a member of the specified class.

# class
[[:alnum:]]
[[:alpha:]]
[[:digit:]]
[[:lower:]]
[[:upper:]]

# Examples
[abc]* any file beginning with either a, b, or c.
BACKUP.[0-9][0-9][0-9] any file beginning with BACKUP, followed by 3 numerals.
[[:upper:]]* any file beginning with one upper letter.
[![:digit:]]* any file not beginning with a numeral.
*[[:digit:]123] any file ending with a lower-case letter or the numeral 1, 2, 3.
